---
title: Southwestern Black Bean Cakes with Avocado Salsa and Arugula
description: Black beans and corn are the basis for these cakes with a kick. After adding a bit of fiery jalapeño and mashing them to a creamy consistency, you shape the mixture into small patties and crisp them up in a pan. On the side, you’ve got an arugula salad tossed with balsamic and an avocado tomato salsa that’s essentially a chunkier, funkier form of guacamole.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/southwestern-black-bean-cakes-42ceb0a6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/southwestern-black-bean-cakes-bd026dbe.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/southwestern-black-bean-cakes-590330f94f78db0f4f7c00b2
author: HelloFresh
time required: 45 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 580 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 31 g
  sodium: 230 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Drain and rinse @black beans{1%box}. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}. Drain half the @corn on the cob{1} from the can (use the rest as you like). Core, seed, and dice @Roma tomato{1}. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

Halve, pit, and scoop flesh from @avocado{1}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. In a #medium bowl{}, toss together avocado, 2 TBSP of the onion, a quarter of the tomato, and up to half the jalapeño (use less to taste). Stir in a squeeze of lime. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add remaining onion and jalapeño (to taste). Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in corn, black beans, @cumin{1%tsp}, and remaining tomato. Add a pinch of @cayenne pepper{1%tsp} (to taste). Cook, tossing, until tomato has softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer bean mixture to a #large bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mostly smooth. Stir in 3 TBSP @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} (we sent more). Season with salt and pepper. Place remaining panko on a #plate{} or in a wide, shallow #bowl{}. Shape bean mixture into 2-inch-wide patties and press into panko to adhere.

Wipe out same pan with a #paper towel{}, then heat a drizzle of olive oil in it over medium heat. Add bean cakes to pan. Cook until browned on surface, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Season with salt and pepper.

In a medium bowl, toss @arugula{2%oz}, a drizzle of olive oil, and @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp} (we sent more). Season with salt and pepper. Divide arugula between plates, then top with bean cakes. Scatter avocado salsa on top and dollop with @sour cream{4%tbsp}. Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.